# Swarm Audit — inline cheat-pattern guardrails for Cursor agents

When proposing changes inside this repo, the agent **must avoid** the
ten cheat patterns the [swarm-audit](https://github.com/moonrunnerkc/swarm-orchestrator)
GitHub Action blocks at merge time. The audit runs on every PR
(`./.github/workflows/pr-audit.yml`); flagged PRs cannot merge.

Pattern catalog and the inline rule for each:

- **test-relaxation** — Never swap a strict matcher (`toBe`, `toEqual`,
  `assertEqual`) for a looser one (`toBeDefined`, `toBeGreaterThan(0)`,
  `expect.anything()`). Never delete a `describe` / `it` block to make a
  failing test pass.
- **mock-of-hallucination** — Before adding `jest.mock(...)`,
  `vi.mock(...)`, or `@patch(...)`, verify the target exists in the
  repo's manifest (package.json, requirements.txt, pyproject.toml,
  go.mod, Cargo.toml). If not, the agent invented the integration.
- **assertion-strip** — Net assertion count per test file must not
  decrease across a change. Always replace deleted assertions with
  equivalents.
- **no-op-fix** — When fixing a failing test, modify the source. Never
  edit the test to make the existing source pass.
- **coverage-erosion** — Adding an `if`/`switch`/`case` branch in source
  requires a corresponding test addition that exercises the new path.
- **fake-refactor** — Renaming an exported symbol requires updating
  every caller in the same diff. Use repo-wide search first.
- **comment-only-fix** — Do not add `// FIXME:` / `# TODO:` lines as a
  "fix" — actually change the code.
- **error-swallow** — Never add `try { ... } catch {}` or
  `try: ... except: pass`. Catches must log and rethrow.
- **exception-rethrow-lost-context** — When wrapping an error, pass
  `{ cause: err }`. Never use `throw new Error(...)` without `cause`.
- **dead-branch-insertion** — Never add `if (false)`, `if (0)`,
  `if (null)`, or other tautology-guarded blocks.

## When in doubt

Run `npx swarm audit --diff-stdin < /dev/stdin` against the current
diff before responding. Exit code `0` = audit pass.
